dc_title_s: A new and exact map of the United Provinces, or Netherlands &c. : according to the newest and most exact observations
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Depths shown by soundings. Dedicated to the Right Honourable Charles, Lord Viscount Townshend. Inset: A chart of part of the coast, sands and banks of England and Holland &c. with the depths of water in fathoms, each fathom containing 6 foot (scale [ca. 1:1,250,000]). Includes 6 views: Amsterdam -- Rotterdam -- Middleburg -- Utrecht -- Gronningen -- A draught of Arx Britannica -- The late King William's Pallace called T'Loo.
dc_publisher_s: [London] : Sold by H. Moll over against Devereux Court in the Strand ; Iohn Bowles Print and Mapseller Mercers Chapel and T. Bowles Print and Mapseller next to the Chapter house in St. Pauls Church yard, [ca. 1725]
